entries.source: VHL (Von Hippel-Lindau Tumor Suppressor) A tumor suppressor protein involved in the regulation of hypoxia. Mutations cause von Hippel-Lindau disease, characterized by multiple tumors.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WAS (Wiskott-Aldrich Syndrome)Белок, участвующий в регуляции актинового цитоскелета. Мутации вызывают синдром Вискотта-Олдрича, характеризующийся иммунодефицитом и тромбоцитопенией.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WAS (Wiskott-Aldrich Syndrome) A protein involved in the regulation of the actin cytoskeleton. Mutations cause Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome, characterized by immunodeficiency and thrombocytopenia.

entries.context: A human readable string that is the recommended default way to present this concept to a user.
entries.source: WNT10A (Wnt Oila a'zosi 10A) embrion rivojlanishi va hujayra proliferatsiyasi uchun muhim bo'lgan Wnt signalizatsiya yo'lida ishtirok etadigan oqsil. Mutatsiyalar turli xil rivojlanish anomaliyalari bilan bog'liq bo'lishi mumkin.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WNT10A (Wnt Family Member 10A)Белок, участвующий в сигнальном пути Wnt, важном для эмбрионального развития и клеточной пролиферации. Мутации могут быть связаны с различными аномалиями развития.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WNT10A (Wnt Family Member 10A)A protein involved in the Wnt signaling pathway, which is important for embryonic development and cell proliferation. Mutations can be associated with various developmental abnormalities.

entries.context: A human readable string that is the recommended default way to present this concept to a user.
entries.source: WRAP53 (TP53ga WD Repeat Containing Antisense to TP53) Telomeraza stabilizatsiyasi va lokalizatsiyasini tartibga soluvchi, shuningdek, DNKni tiklash jarayonida rol o'ynaydigan oqsil. Mutatsiyalar turli kasalliklar, jumladan, diskeroz konjenit bilan bog'liq.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WRAP53 (WD Repeat Containing Antisense to TP53)Белок, регулирующий стабилизацию и локализацию теломеразы, а также играющий роль в процессе репарации ДНК. Мутации связаны с различными заболеваниями, включая дискерозис конгенита.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WRAP53 (WD Repeat Containing Antisense to TP53)A protein that regulates telomerase stabilization and localization, and also plays a role in DNA repair. Mutations are associated with various diseases, including dyskerosis congenita.

entries.source: WRN Verner sindromi RecQ Helicase kabi) Helikaz genomik barqarorlikni saqlashda ishtirok etadi. Mutatsiyalar Verner sindromini keltirib chiqaradi, bu erta qarish va saraton xavfining oshishi bilan tavsiflanadi.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WRN Werner Syndrome RecQ Like Helicase) Геликаза, участвующая в поддержании геномной стабильности. Мутации вызывают синдром Вернера, характеризующийся преждевременным старением и повышенным риском рака.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WRN Werner Syndrome RecQ Like Helicase) A helicase involved in maintaining genomic stability. Mutations cause Werner syndrome, characterized by premature aging and an increased risk of cancer.

entries.source: WT1 (Wilms Tumor 1) Buyrak va jinsiy bez rivojlanishida rol o'ynaydigan transkripsiya omili. Mutatsiyalar Wilms shishi va boshqa sindromlar bilan bog'liq.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WT1 (Wilms Tumor 1)Транскрипционный фактор, играющий роль в развитии почек и гонад. Мутации связаны с опухолью Вильмса и другими синдромами.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: WT1 (Wilms Tumor 1)A transcription factor that plays a role in the development of the kidneys and gonads. Mutations are associated with Wilms tumor and other syndromes.

entries.source: XPA (Xeroderma Pigmentosum, Komplementatsiya guruhi A) ultrabinafsha nurlanish natijasida kelib chiqqan DNK shikastlanishini tiklashda ishtirok etadigan oqsil. Mutatsiyalar ultrabinafsha nurlanishiga yuqori sezuvchanlik va teri saratoni xavfi bilan tavsiflangan kseroderma pigmentozini keltirib chiqaradi.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: XPA (Xeroderma Pigmentosum, Complementation Group A) Белок, участвующий в репарации повреждений ДНК, вызванных ультрафиолетовым излучением. Мутации вызывают ксеродерму пигментозу, характеризующуюся повышенной чувствительностью к ультрафиолету и риском рака кожи.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: XPA (Xeroderma Pigmentosum, Complementation Group A) A protein involved in the repair of DNA damage caused by ultraviolet radiation. Mutations cause xeroderma pigmentosis, characterized by increased sensitivity to ultraviolet radiation and the risk of skin cancer.

entries.source: XPC (Xeroderma Pigmentosum, Komplementatsiya guruhi C) DNKning nukleotidlar eksizyonini tiklash jarayonida ishtirok etadigan oqsil. Mutatsiyalar kseroderma pigmentozini ham keltirib chiqaradi.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: XPC (Xeroderma Pigmentosum, Complementation Group C) Белок, участвующий в процессе нуклеотидной эксцизионной репарации ДНК. Мутации также вызывают ксеродерму пигментозу.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
entries.source: XPC (Xeroderma Pigmentosum, Complementation Group C) A protein involved in the process of nucleotide excision repair of DNA. Mutations also cause xeroderma pigmentosis.

entries.context: The text value for this designation.
